      <ul style="list-style:none; padding:0; margin:0; font-size:0.85rem; color:#991b1b; display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:0.3rem;">
        <li>• Never administer undiluted potassium chloride (KCl) IV — fatal arrhythmia risk</li>
        <li>• Correct hyponatraemia slowly (max 8–10 mEq/L/24 hr) to prevent osmotic demyelination syndrome</li>
        <li>• In COPD/CO₂ retainers: target SpO₂ 88–92% to avoid suppressing hypoxic drive</li>
        <li>• Always verify serum K⁺ and Mg²⁺ before administering digoxin</li>
        <li>• IV magnesium sulphate must be administered slowly — monitor for loss of deep tendon reflexes (early toxicity sign)</li>
